title: Patricia Breen At the Museum Santa Ornament
description:
Ornament developed from Edward Kemeys’ Lions, 1893 and main entrance, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

With her signature artistic detail, Patricia Breen honors the Art Institute of Chicago and the city's beloved Lions, 1893 by Edward Kemeys, bedecked for the holidays. This one-of-a-kind limited edition Santa is mouth-blown, then meticulously hand-painted and hand-silvered in Krakow, Poland. 

  • Dimensions: 6.5 x 2.75 x 1.75 in.
  • Materials: Glass
  • Hand painted and silvered.
  • Made in Poland
